writing.title: If you know she’s yours then why don’t you act like it?
writing.body:
I would venture to say that *most* (not all) of us lifestylers are made ultimately needing the ownership or being owned. Words like “Sir”; “good girl” are yummy words but the desire & need for “my” or “mine” is the ultimate. Those that like to play Dominant or submissive don’t need those qualifiers or terms of possession. They seem to be able to keep things compartmentalized in scene and out of scene. I am just not able to do that, nor do I want to.

We all come across those kindred spirits that we seemingly connect with instantaneously. Like something cosmic is at play, fate or the gods have destined paths to cross. When we (perspective of subs) are told things like “my” or “mine”; the melting begins. If you have been around Fet anytime at all, this is very common to be heard from Doms/Sirs. 

I personally have had a few connections and very good connections but…….. they misfired, didn’t fire, or didn’t last. Yet the Doms/Sirs have made declarations of ownership or saying I know I belong to them. Like it’s supposed to hypnotize me and I am to begin chanting, “Yes Sir, I am yours. Yes Sir, I am yours. Yes Sir, I am yours.” Except I don’t or can’t, why not?

I’ll give you some reasons why I don’t accept that declaration of ownership.

• You have hurt me and I have pulled away or shut down

• You failed to make the “extra” effort as to find out why I have pulled away or shut down(I assure you I’m a good communicator and there were a hundred conversations before I pulled away)

• You have not met my needs and I’m tired of trying to explain it

• You engage with me inconsistently, this is a biggie for me

• I’m not emotionally safe with you

• Your actions show me something different than what your words say

If you know that she is yours or at the very least ***should be***, then why isn’t she? Are you too quick to point at her and say, “Offender, she is the reason!”? Submissives are built to belong to someone(s), if she doesn’t belong to you, that falls on your shoulders as to why. You are the Dom, it’s your job, your responsibility to create an environment and relationship in which her only response is to submit. If she’s defensive, why? If she’s sensitive, why? If she’s angry, why? If she’s scared, why? She’s going to try everything she knows and is capable of to serve and submit. It’s not about submissiveness being a gift that she chooses. Dominance & submissiveness are equally gifts. 

If you know she’s yours then why don’t you act like it?
